Hadron Collider Physics with CDF

  Particle Physics at the Highest Available Energies

   The CDF Group at LBNL is involved in the following aspects of the CDF
   experiment at the Tevatron proton-antiproton collider at Fermilab.
     __________________________________________________________________

   PHYSICS GOALS

   [orangedot.gif] Measure properties of Top Quark
   [orangedot.gif] Precision Electroweak Physics
   [orangedot.gif] Study of B Mesons
   [orangedot.gif] Search for New Phenomena

   EXPERIMENTAL TECHNIQUES

   [orangedot.gif] Development of high precision Silicon Vertex Detectors
   [orangedot.gif] Work on Central Tracking Chamber for CDF II
   [orangedot.gif] Computing for Run II

   These developments will be needed for future hadron collider
   experiments such as the ATLAS detector at LHC (see also the ATLAS Page
   at LBNL ).
